This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. Christy Anyanwu  Ade Bakare Couture’s on-going exhibition at Terra Culture,Victoria Island, Lagos is  a retrospective of the ace London-based designer’s work of over 25 years. Talking with The Sun Newspapers recently, the ace designer acknowledged that, “This is not his first time staging an exhibition . I had one when I celebrated five years, 15 years and 20 years consecutively. “I feel it is very important to inspire others especially the younger generation, and for them to see how your creativity can lead to a successful profession and life. In Africa.” He said his label tended to focus more on careers such as lawyers, doctors, engineers amongst others. According to him, the modern world has shown how people in the creative industry such as music, food, interior design etc have established companies worldwide. The idea of the exhibition is to identify, stimulate and encourage creativity in people regardless of fashion. READ ALSO: Gov. Emmanuel donates N48m to corps members, camp officials “The exhibition is open to the public from Sunday 11th to 16th of November 2018 from 10am to 8pm at Terra Kulture on Tamiyu savage in Victoria Island, Lagos. “We are bringing in students from local schools to attend, I feel usually these are the children who do not get the opportunity to travel far and see lots of exhibitions. “Two schools a day with 50 students per school are targeted both from the island and mainland axis in Lagos state”.